this little ream job here.

501
00:28:48.375 --> 00:28:49.375
"Ream job"?

502
00:28:50.166 --> 00:28:52.041
Talking-to. You know?

503
00:28:52.208 --> 00:28:55.708
Stern boss-lady over here.
Can't be the fun friend.

504
00:28:55.833 --> 00:28:57.083
(CHUCKLES)

505
00:28:57.208 --> 00:28:58.583
But mega-serious face
right now.

506
00:28:59.166 --> 00:29:01.416
Your hobby is causing
your work to suffer.

507
00:29:01.541 --> 00:29:03.625
(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

508
00:29:08.916 --> 00:29:10.833
How about we just ignore that
for a minute. okay?

509
00:29:11.916 --> 00:29:13.416
This obsession with swords.

510
00:29:13.541 --> 00:29:17.416
um. it's not a good look
for Human Resources.

511
00:29:17.583 --> 00:29:19.958
In fact. I'm going
to have to fire you

512
00:29:20.083 --> 00:29:21.791
if you don't
get your shit together.

513
00:29:22.041 --> 00:29:24.625
Oh. so this is like. um...

514
00:29:24.750 --> 00:29:25.875
like an ultimatum.

515
00:29:26.250 --> 00:29:28.791
Yes. Okay. Yeah. you get it.

516
00:29:28.916 --> 00:29:31.833
Whew! Conflict
is not my strong point.

517
00:29:31.958 --> 00:29:33.458
Uh. you will be terminated

518
00:29:33.583 --> 00:29:35.500
if you don't stop looking
for weapons on the clock.

519
00:29:35.666 --> 00:29:38.666
You're freaking people out.
Especially Darryl.

520
00:29:42.375 --> 00:29:44.666
God. I hate Darryl.

521
00:29:45.666 --> 00:29:48.500
Look. you don't understand.

522
00:29:48.666 --> 00:29:51.041
I am nothing
without that sword.

523
00:29:51.166 --> 00:29:53.208
(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

524
00:29:55.083 --> 00:29:57.250
Okay. moment of truth.

525
00:29:57.416 --> 00:29:59.666
Are you going
to live here in reality

526
00:29:59.833 --> 00:30:01.625
or are you just going
to waste your life away

527
00:30:01.750 --> 00:30:03.416
like some kind
of daydream Jimmy.

528
00:30:03.583 --> 00:30:04.583
not having any goals.

529
00:30:04.708 --> 00:30:06.375
not having any way
to stop yourself

530
00:30:06.500 --> 00:30:08.083
from touching the phone.
I can see your hand.

531
00:30:08.208 --> 00:30:09.208
If I could just touch it
for one second.

532
00:30:09.333 --> 00:30:10.666
-No. Just don't pick it up.
-Just see what it says.

533
00:30:10.791 --> 00:30:11.958
-Just. like. please don't.
-And I could just...

534
00:30:12.083 --> 00:30:13.125
-I'm doing it.
-Actually. don't...

535
00:30:13.250 --> 00:30:14.458
Okay. you did it. All right.

536
00:30:14.625 --> 00:30:16.625
(ETHEREAL MUSICAL STING)

537
00:30:17.916 --> 00:30:19.333
-Adam?
-Oh. wow.

538
00:30:20.166 --> 00:30:21.333
-Adam? Wait.
-I got to go.

539
00:30:21.500 --> 00:30:22.833
Adam? You can't just...

540
00:30:23.000 --> 00:30:24.125
If you walk out that door.

541
00:30:24.250 --> 00:30:25.916
you can
kiss this place goodbye.

542
00:30:26.333 --> 00:30:27.500
Consensually.

543
00:30:27.625 --> 00:30:29.125
(CARS HONKING)

544
00:30:32.583 --> 00:30:34.833
ADAM: Okay. uh.
I think I'm here.

545
00:30:35.000 --> 00:30:36.250
MAN: <i>Meet me inside.</i>

546
00:30:37.041 --> 00:30:40.208
(CHUCKLES) Well.
how will I know it's...

547
00:30:40.375 --> 00:30:42.708
-MAN: <i>You'll know.</i>
-(CALL DISCONNECTS)

548
00:30:43.875 --> 00:30:45.958
(MUSIC PLAYING FAINTLY)

549
00:30:51.458 --> 00:30:53.166
-(DOOR OPENS)
-(BELL JINGLES)

550
00:30:56.250 --> 00:30:57.250
(ADAM SIGHS)

551
00:31:01.458 --> 00:31:02.958
-(DOOR OPENS)
-(BELL JINGLES)

552
00:31:09.291 --> 00:31:10.791
(WHISPERS) It's you. right?

553
00:31:13.708 --> 00:31:15.625
Pretty sure. Yeah.

554
00:31:16.541 --> 00:31:17.583
-Tight.
-(CHUCKLES)

555
00:31:17.708 --> 00:31:19.250
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

556
00:31:20.250 --> 00:31:21.291
You have my sword?

557
00:31:22.000 --> 00:31:24.291
No. I don't think so.

558
00:31:24.958 --> 00:31:26.083
(IN NORMAL TONE) No sword?

559
00:31:27.000 --> 00:31:28.000
No.

560
00:31:29.333 --> 00:31:30.958
(SIGHS) Oh. God.

561
00:31:31.125 --> 00:31:33.250
Okay. well.
then you're not you.

562
00:31:34.083 --> 00:31:35.625
-Sorry.
-Yeah. (SIGHS)

563
00:31:37.541 --> 00:31:38.541
(GASPS)

564
00:31:40.916 --> 00:31:42.833
-You got my sword?
-What?

565
00:31:43.625 --> 00:31:44.666
Never mind.

566
00:31:45.583 --> 00:31:47.000
(KNOCKING)

567
00:31:54.458 --> 00:31:56.583
(WHISPERS) Have you
got my sword?

568
00:31:57.583 --> 00:31:59.000
Me. It's me.

569
00:31:59.791 --> 00:32:01.125
What the hell. man?

570
00:32:01.291 --> 00:32:02.250
You literally asked

571
00:32:02.375 --> 00:32:03.625
everyone in the store
if they got a sword?

572
00:32:03.791 --> 00:32:05.458
Yeah. Well. they all look like
they have swords.

573
00:32:05.625 --> 00:32:07.875
I have a wizard's staff
at home.

574
00:32:08.791 --> 00:32:10.375
Get away from him.

575
00:32:12.083 --> 00:32:14.333
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

576
00:32:17.458 --> 00:32:20.041
(MAN VOCALIZES DRAMATICALLY)

577
00:32:20.166 --> 00:32:21.375
(ADAM GASPS)

578
00:32:29.958 --> 00:32:31.916
This is as far
as I can take you.

579
00:32:32.833 --> 00:32:33.833
What?

580
00:32:35.000 --> 00:32:36.750
Wh-What am I supposed
to do with that?

581
00:32:36.875 --> 00:32:37.875
(LAUGHS)

582
00:32:38.791 --> 00:32:40.291
Your problem. dude.

583
00:32:40.666 --> 00:32:42.208
I was never here.

584
00:32:46.583 --> 00:32:48.791
TOY: <i>Situation under control!</i>

585
00:32:55.125 --> 00:32:57.333
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES)

586
00:33:02.250 --> 00:33:03.958
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

587
00:33:12.208 --> 00:33:14.250
(ADAM STRAINING)

588
00:33:22.625 --> 00:33:25.000
Hey. you can't do that!

589
00:33:25.333 --> 00:33:28.208
Oh. don't worry.
Uh. the Sword's mine.

590
00:33:29.166 --> 00:33:30.166
Okay.

591
00:33:30.291 --> 00:33:32.625
(STRAINS)

592
00:33:32.750 --> 00:33:34.000
-(CREAKS)
-Oh.

593
00:33:34.125 --> 00:33:35.958
Oh. no. Oh. no. (EXCLAIMS)

594
00:33:36.083 --> 00:33:37.291
-(GROANS)
-(PATRONS EXCLAIM)

595
00:33:37.416 --> 00:33:39.875
-(GROANS)
-Sir. please get off of Torak.

596
00:33:40.041 --> 00:33:41.625
ADAM: Torak is on me.

597
00:33:41.750 --> 00:33:42.833
(STRAINS)

598
00:33:45.458 --> 00:33:47.500
Got it. Not got it.
I don't got it.

599
00:33:47.666 --> 00:33:50.125
Sir. please stop
ravishing the pillager.

600
00:33:50.291 --> 00:33:52.416
ADAM: He's ravishing me. Ugh!

601
00:33:53.375 --> 00:33:54.833
-(GRUNTING)
-(PHONE BEEPS)

602
00:33:56.000 --> 00:33:57.250
Sir. that sword
is not for sale.

603
00:33:57.416 --> 00:34:00.375
I'm not buying it.
I'm taking it.

604
00:34:00.625 --> 00:34:03.000
-(ALL EXCLAIM)
-(ADAM PANTING)

605
00:34:07.708 --> 00:34:10.291
In just a second.
I'm going to vanish

606
00:34:10.458 --> 00:34:13.500
into a brilliant
blast of light.

607
00:34:14.250 --> 00:34:15.250
Or something.

608
00:34:15.583 --> 00:34:16.833
Cool.

609
00:34:16.958 --> 00:34:18.208
(MUSIC CRESCENDOING)

610
00:34:18.333 --> 00:34:20.541
By the Power of Grayskull.

611
00:34:20.916 --> 00:34:24.416
(VOICE CRACKING)
I have to go home!

612
00:34:24.541 --> 00:34:27.000
-(MUSIC STOPS)
-(PANTING)

613
00:34:33.916 --> 00:34:38.250
Grayskull. just...
take me home.

614
00:34:44.083 --> 00:34:46.416
(STIRRING ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

615
00:34:46.541 --> 00:34:47.750
(GRUNTS)

616
00:34:48.125 --> 00:34:49.333
Are you single?

617
00:34:49.458 --> 00:34:51.375
-(BELL JINGLES)
-(GRUNTING EXCITEDLY)

618
00:35:00.500 --> 00:35:02.375
-(PEDESTRIANS EXCLAIM)
-(TIRES SCREECH)

619
00:35:03.083 --> 00:35:04.250
(CAR HONKS)

620
00:35:04.375 --> 00:35:06.458
-(BIKE BELL DINGS)
-Hey. what the hell?

621
00:35:08.750 --> 00:35:10.541
WOMAN ON TV: <i>I hate it</i>
<i>when you make me laugh.</i>

622
00:35:10.666 --> 00:35:12.416
<i>Even worse</i>
<i>when you make me cry.</i>

623
00:35:12.541 --> 00:35:14.250
-(SOBBING)
-(DOOR UNLOCKS)

624
00:35:14.375 --> 00:35:15.375
-(CLEARING THROAT)
<i>-I hate it</i>

625
00:35:15.500 --> 00:35:17.541
<i>when you're not around and</i>
<i>the fact that you didn't call.</i>

626
00:35:17.666 --> 00:35:19.916
-Uh. is that the...
-Sword of Power?

627
00:35:20.041 --> 00:35:23.666
(PANTING) Yeah. it is. Okay.

628
00:35:27.750 --> 00:35:28.750
Please work.

629
00:35:31.750 --> 00:35:32.958
Do something.

630
00:35:46.458 --> 00:35:47.875
(SNORES SOFTLY)

631
00:35:48.000 --> 00:35:49.833
-(KNOCKING ON DOOR)
-(INHALES DEEPLY)

632
00:35:50.583 --> 00:35:52.000
(DOOR OPENS)

633
00:35:53.458 --> 00:35:55.541
(DRAMATIC ROCK MUSIC PLAYS)

634
00:35:59.416 --> 00:36:00.500
(SIGHS)

635
00:36:03.666 --> 00:36:05.083
Great.

636
00:36:05.416 --> 00:36:07.791
(GROOVY ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

637
00:36:07.916 --> 00:36:10.750
-Hey. cool sword. Highlander.
-(BOTH LAUGH)

638
00:36:11.208 --> 00:36:13.125
OFFICER 1: Yeah. nice sword
there. Rip Van...

639
00:36:13.250 --> 00:36:14.916
uh. King Arth...

640
00:36:15.250 --> 00:36:17.791
(CLEARS THROAT) What even
are you? H-Highlander?

641
00:36:24.416 --> 00:36:25.625
(DRIVERS SHOUTING
IN ANNOYANCE)

642
00:36:25.750 --> 00:36:27.750
(CARS HONKING)

643
00:36:27.875 --> 00:36:30.875
<i>(THE POWER</i> BY SNAP! PLAYING
ON CAR SPEAKERS)

644
00:36:36.333 --> 00:36:40.208
God. what... what the hell?
Idiots. man.

645
00:36:41.666 --> 00:36:42.666
Hang tight.

646
00:36:44.666 --> 00:36:46.583
(DISTANT COMMOTION)

647
00:36:48.083 --> 00:36:50.541
(PEOPLE SCREAMING
AND CLAMORING)

648
00:36:51.458 --> 00:36:53.000
What is going on?

649
00:36:54.541 --> 00:36:57.000
<i>(WHAT'S UP?</i>
BY 4 NON BLONDES PLAYING)

650
00:36:59.916 --> 00:37:01.958
(ROARS)

651
00:37:08.666 --> 00:37:10.458
-(GASPS)
-(ALARM WAILING)

652
00:37:13.833 --> 00:37:14.916
(GASPING)

653
00:37:18.083 --> 00:37:19.083
No.

654
00:37:20.291 --> 00:37:21.541
(ROARS)

655
00:37:23.791 --> 00:37:25.500
(GRUNTS. PANTS)

656
00:37:29.125 --> 00:37:30.125
Okay.

657
00:37:30.583 --> 00:37:32.166
(ROARS)

658
00:37:36.958 --> 00:37:38.166
(PANTING)

659
00:37:41.791 --> 00:37:43.416
(PANTING TIREDLY)

660
00:37:52.041 --> 00:37:53.083
(HEAVY THUD)

661
00:37:53.916 --> 00:37:55.208
(GROANS)

662
00:37:56.125 --> 00:37:58.125
(THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING)

663
00:37:59.958 --> 00:38:01.583
(ROARS)

664
00:38:03.500 --> 00:38:04.916
(PANTS)

665
00:38:06.041 --> 00:38:07.041
(GROANS)

666
00:38:07.166 --> 00:38:08.166
(GRUNTS)

667
00:38:09.125 --> 00:38:10.833
(GROANING)

668
00:38:11.458 --> 00:38:12.458
(ADAM COUGHS)

669
00:38:12.583 --> 00:38:13.833
-(TIRES SCREECH)
-(CAR CRASHES)

670
00:38:15.416 --> 00:38:16.916
(PANTING)

671
00:38:17.041 --> 00:38:19.125
(THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES)

672
00:38:19.750 --> 00:38:21.750
(ROARS)

673
00:38:23.458 --> 00:38:25.000
(EPIC MUSIC PLAYING)

674
00:38:25.125 --> 00:38:26.708
(GRUNTING)

675
00:38:29.083 --> 00:38:30.583
-(WEAPON POWERS UP)
-(ROARS)

676
00:38:42.791 --> 00:38:43.791
Adam?

677
00:38:43.916 --> 00:38:45.000
(PANTS)

678
00:38:45.125 --> 00:38:46.208
Is it really you?

679
00:38:46.375 --> 00:38:47.375
What?

680
00:38:48.625 --> 00:38:50.333
You don't recognize me?

681
00:38:52.041 --> 00:38:53.041
Huh?

682
00:38:53.750 --> 00:38:55.833
Still such a squink.

683
00:38:58.041 --> 00:38:59.041
Teela?

684
00:39:02.250 --> 00:39:03.250
Ready to go home?

685
00:39:03.916 --> 00:39:04.958
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

686
00:39:05.958 --> 00:39:07.416
-(TEELA GRUNTS)
-(GROWLS)

687
00:39:10.291 --> 00:39:11.750
(GRUNTING)

688
00:39:12.583 --> 00:39:13.583
(GROWLS)

689
00:39:13.708 --> 00:39:15.125
(GASPING)

690
00:39:15.625 --> 00:39:16.833
(ROARS)

691
00:39:18.500 --> 00:39:19.958
(GRUNTS)

692
00:39:21.250 --> 00:39:23.458
(PANTING)

693
00:39:24.750 --> 00:39:25.833
(GRUNTS)

694
00:39:27.208 --> 00:39:28.833
(ADAM GRUNTS)

695
00:39:31.000 --> 00:39:32.500
(BOTH PANTING)

696
00:39:33.583 --> 00:39:35.458
(ADAM WHEEZING)

697
00:39:36.916 --> 00:39:38.250
(BEAST MAN GROWLS)

698
00:39:40.666 --> 00:39:42.833
(SNIFFING)

699
00:39:45.125 --> 00:39:46.125
(GROWLS)

700
00:39:46.708 --> 00:39:47.791
(GRUNTS)

701
00:39:49.458 --> 00:39:50.583
(CAR CRASHES)

702
00:39:51.791 --> 00:39:53.375
What does that thing
want with me?

703
00:39:54.041 --> 00:39:55.875
It's not you he's after.
It's this.

704
00:39:56.000 --> 00:39:57.958
(ADAM PANTING)

705
00:39:58.083 --> 00:39:59.500
The Sword sent a signal.

706
00:39:59.625 --> 00:40:01.375
What took you so long
to raise it?

707
00:40:01.500 --> 00:40:03.291
I... I kind of misplaced it.

708
00:40:03.708 --> 00:40:05.333
-"Misplaced"?
-Yeah.

709
00:40:05.458 --> 00:40:06.500
It's been 15 years.

710
00:40:06.625 --> 00:40:08.708
-(CAR SHATTERING)
-(WOMAN SCREAMS)

711
00:40:11.791 --> 00:40:13.625
Okay. on the count of three.

712
00:40:14.000 --> 00:40:15.916
-No. No. I don't want to run.
-One. Two.

713
00:40:16.041 --> 00:40:17.041
I can't do it.

714
00:40:17.166 --> 00:40:18.625
-Three. Come on.
-I don't have it in me.

715
00:40:18.750 --> 00:40:20.500
(EPIC MUSIC PLAYING)

716
00:40:20.625 --> 00:40:22.166
(CAR ALARM BLARING)

717
00:40:23.125 --> 00:40:24.916
(PANTING)

718
00:40:26.750 --> 00:40:28.416
All right. slow down.
slow down.

719
00:40:28.875 --> 00:40:30.458
-TEELA: Jump!
-What? No!

720
00:40:31.166 --> 00:40:32.166
(GRUNTS)

721
00:40:34.416 --> 00:40:37.083
Okay. okay. Okay.

722
00:40:38.125 --> 00:40:39.250
(GRUNTS. YELPS)

723
00:40:40.208 --> 00:40:41.208
(GRUNTS)

724
00:40:41.333 --> 00:40:42.416
-(CAR HONKING)
-(GASPS)

725
00:40:42.541 --> 00:40:43.833
(SCREAMS)

726
00:40:43.958 --> 00:40:45.625
-(CRIES OUT)
-(TIRES SCREECH)

727
00:40:46.250 --> 00:40:48.583
-What's wrong with you?
-Yeah. Okay. (WHIMPERS)

728
00:40:51.000 --> 00:40:52.000
(FEET THUD)

729
00:40:53.416 --> 00:40:54.958
(ROARS)

730
00:40:56.708 --> 00:40:58.166
(PEOPLE SCREAM)

731
00:41:02.125 --> 00:41:03.291
Where are we going?

732
00:41:03.583 --> 00:41:05.583
My ship. Up there.

733
00:41:06.291 --> 00:41:07.416
Up where?

734
00:41:08.625 --> 00:41:10.625
(ADAM PANTING)

735
00:41:13.750 --> 00:41:14.708
Oh.

736
00:41:15.416 --> 00:41:17.208
-TEELA: Yeah.
-(CROWD CHATTERING)

737
00:41:17.333 --> 00:41:18.333
Cool.

738
00:41:19.000 --> 00:41:20.583
TEELA: Ship. Open up.

739
00:41:20.750 --> 00:41:22.333
SHIP: <i>Opening hull door.</i>

740
00:41:27.833 --> 00:41:30.458
No. you know what.
I told you guys it was real.

741
00:41:32.250 --> 00:41:35.208
Not you guys specifically.

742
00:41:35.375 --> 00:41:38.083
just. you know.
you kind of represent. like.

743
00:41:38.208 --> 00:41:39.833
a lot of the people in my life
who doubted me.

744
00:41:39.958 --> 00:41:41.708
-(BEAST MAN ROARS)
-(CROWD SCREAMING)

745
00:41:41.833 --> 00:41:43.083
Adam. come on.

746
00:41:43.208 --> 00:41:45.625
(HEROIC SYNTH-ROCK
MUSIC PLAYING)

747
00:41:49.250 --> 00:41:50.375
(GROWLS)

748
00:41:54.583 --> 00:41:57.333
Ship. let's get out of here.
Now!

749
00:41:57.750 --> 00:41:58.958
SHIP: <i>Getting out of here now.</i>

750
00:41:59.458 --> 00:42:01.208
(CROWD EXCLAIMING)

751
00:42:02.583 --> 00:42:04.291
-(ALL SCREAM)
-(DOG BARKING)

752
00:42:04.416 --> 00:42:05.500
(ROARS)

753
00:42:07.291 --> 00:42:09.416
Hang on.
It's about to get weird.

754
00:42:09.791 --> 00:42:12.208
-Okay.
-Ship. fold space.

755
00:42:12.500 --> 00:42:14.125
SHIP: <i>Folding space</i>
<i>and getting weird.</i>

756
00:42:16.958 --> 00:42:18.708
(LAUGHING)

757
00:42:18.833 --> 00:42:21.208
(HEROIC ROCK MUSIC CONTINUES)

758
00:42:21.333 --> 00:42:23.208
(PANTING)

759
00:42:23.791 --> 00:42:24.791
(CHUCKLES)

760
00:42:35.916 --> 00:42:37.208
(EXHALES)

761
00:42:40.166 --> 00:42:41.791
I can't believe it's you.

762
00:42:42.708 --> 00:42:44.083
Yeah. (CHUCKLES)

763
00:42:44.791 --> 00:42:47.375
-It's me.
-You've gotten so big.

764
00:42:49.666 --> 00:42:50.833
As in you've aged.

765
00:42:52.541 --> 00:42:55.416
Well! You've aged well.
You've... You've grown older!

766
00:42:55.541 --> 00:42:57.125
(LAUGHS)

767
00:42:57.250 --> 00:42:58.958
And you haven't
changed at all.

768
00:42:59.833 --> 00:43:01.541
-Well...
-(CHUCKLES)

769
00:43:05.666 --> 00:43:07.666
Adam. you don't know
how bad it's been.

770
00:43:08.125 --> 00:43:11.666
I mean. everything changed
since you left.

771
00:43:11.833 --> 00:43:12.833
My parents?

772
00:43:15.500 --> 00:43:18.291
Skeletor took them
that night.

773
00:43:19.458 --> 00:43:22.208
and. um.
we never saw them again.

774
00:43:23.000 --> 00:43:25.375
SHIP: <i>Arriving at Eternia</i>
<i>in ten.</i>

775
00:43:25.916 --> 00:43:29.541
<i>nine. eight. seven. six...</i>

776
00:43:29.666 --> 00:43:31.416
I can't believe
I'm finally home.

777
00:43:32.458 --> 00:43:34.583
I would manage
your expectations.

778
00:43:34.708 --> 00:43:36.875
SHIP: <i>...two. one.</i>

779
00:43:42.625 --> 00:43:44.458
(MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

780
00:43:48.291 --> 00:43:49.500
ADAM: It's all gone.

781
00:43:53.666 --> 00:43:56.083
TEELA: Skeletor
never wanted Eternos.

782
00:43:56.250 --> 00:43:58.666
He just didn't want
anyone else to have it.

783
00:43:59.916 --> 00:44:01.416
Why would he do this?

784
00:44:01.875 --> 00:44:03.333
Because he's bad.

785
00:44:05.416 --> 00:44:07.583
There's got to be
more to it than that.

786
00:44:09.041 --> 00:44:10.833
He has a skull for a face.

787
00:44:12.000 --> 00:44:13.625
We have to leave.

788
00:44:13.750 --> 00:44:15.916
It's too dangerous
to be out in the open.

789
00:44:16.041 --> 00:44:18.291
(DEVICE BEEPING)

790
00:44:18.416 --> 00:44:20.416
(FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING)

791
00:44:27.583 --> 00:44:29.583
(SNORTING)

792
00:44:37.375 --> 00:44:39.083
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

793
00:44:55.416 --> 00:44:57.416
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

794
00:45:06.250 --> 00:45:07.541
(SNIFFING)

795
00:45:08.958 --> 00:45:10.500
-(SQUEALS)
-What are you looking at?

796
00:45:10.625 --> 00:45:11.916
PIG BOY: Sorry. sir.

797
00:45:12.041 --> 00:45:13.875
I wasn't sure if you were
awake or not. my lord.

798
00:45:14.000 --> 00:45:16.375
Fetch my staff. swine.

799
00:45:16.500 --> 00:45:17.625
PIG BOY: Yes. sir.

800
00:45:17.791 --> 00:45:19.583
Careful! If you drop it.

801
00:45:19.708 --> 00:45:21.875
I'll have you ground
into sausage meat.

802
00:45:22.000 --> 00:45:23.458
just like your mother.

803
00:45:23.583 --> 00:45:24.791
(WHIMPERS)

804
00:45:26.416 --> 00:45:28.083
EVIL-LYN: My lord. Skeletor...

805
00:45:29.958 --> 00:45:32.750
the beast has returned.

806
00:45:39.666 --> 00:45:42.750
BEAST MAN: Oh. vile
and villainous Skeletor.

807
00:45:43.125 --> 00:45:45.791
Sadistic Overlord of Evil...

808
00:45:45.958 --> 00:45:49.958
Oh. do shut up! On your knees.

809
00:45:52.875 --> 00:45:53.958
Lower.

810
00:45:54.083 --> 00:45:56.166
-(CRACKLES)
-Lower.

811
00:45:56.583 --> 00:45:57.583
(BEAST MAN GROANS)

812
00:45:57.916 --> 00:45:59.916
Lower.

813
00:46:00.541 --> 00:46:02.458
Tell me you have the Sword.

814
00:46:02.625 --> 00:46:05.500
I found it. my lord.
but the woman. Teela. took it.

815
00:46:05.625 --> 00:46:08.750
Please stop.
This really hurts. my lord.

816
00:46:09.208 --> 00:46:10.333
Teela?

817
00:46:10.458 --> 00:46:12.875
The whelp
of the King's Man-At-Arms.

818
00:46:13.000 --> 00:46:16.125
Intelligence reports her ship
flying recon over Eternos

819
00:46:16.250 --> 00:46:17.333
just this morning.

820
00:46:17.625 --> 00:46:19.250
Then the Sword is here.

821
00:46:19.416 --> 00:46:22.333
We must follow her
and see where she runs.

822
00:46:22.500 --> 00:46:24.583
That is already in hand.
my lord.

823
00:46:24.708 --> 00:46:25.708
SKELETOR: Mm.

824
00:46:29.916 --> 00:46:31.208
Why are you still here?

825
00:46:31.333 --> 00:46:34.916
Bring me that sword.
you hirsute half-wit!

826
00:46:35.041 --> 00:46:36.958
(SKELETOR SIGHS)

827
00:46:37.083 --> 00:46:40.750
What am I. Evil-Lyn?
Am I not mighty?

828
00:46:40.875 --> 00:46:44.750
My lord.
you are the mightiest.

829
00:46:44.875 --> 00:46:46.416
Have I not gone
out of my way

830
00:46:46.541 --> 00:46:47.875
to show
the people of Eternia

831
00:46:48.000 --> 00:46:51.125
that I am a just
and worthy ruler?

832
00:46:51.291 --> 00:46:54.041
You have killed thousands
of them to prove it.

833
00:46:54.208 --> 00:46:56.708
Oh. but what is it worth?

834
00:46:56.833 --> 00:46:58.916
My lord. if I may?

835
00:46:59.041 --> 00:47:00.041
(GROANS)

836
00:47:00.166 --> 00:47:02.666
You have already won.

837
00:47:02.833 --> 00:47:05.208
You have a vast army
at your command.

838
00:47:05.333 --> 00:47:09.208
Your Staff of Havoc.
your throne of bones.

839
00:47:09.333 --> 00:47:12.166
you have... me.

840
00:47:13.291 --> 00:47:15.583
Do you really need more?

841
00:47:15.750 --> 00:47:18.291
It can all be taken away.
Don't you see?

842
00:47:18.708 --> 00:47:20.208
My Staff can be taken away.

843
00:47:20.333 --> 00:47:22.125
You can be taken away.
All of it.

844
00:47:22.291 --> 00:47:25.541
And then. what am I?

845
00:47:25.833 --> 00:47:27.041
My lord. you are...

846
00:47:27.166 --> 00:47:28.666
-Then I am nothing.
-(GASPS)

847
00:47:28.791 --> 00:47:30.625
-(SKIN SEARING)
-As long as that sword

848
00:47:30.750 --> 00:47:32.875
remains
in someone else's hand.

849
00:47:33.041 --> 00:47:35.500
any power I have
is only temporary.

850
00:47:35.625 --> 00:47:36.625
(BREATH TREMBLING)

851
00:47:36.750 --> 00:47:38.625
I need more than impermanence.

852
00:47:39.500 --> 00:47:41.458
I am no mere king.

853
00:47:42.083 --> 00:47:43.500
I am a devil.

854
00:47:43.916 --> 00:47:46.583
but I mean to be a god.

855
00:47:46.708 --> 00:47:47.916
-(EVIL-LYN GASPS)
-(SEARING)

856
00:47:48.500 --> 00:47:49.833
-(GRUNTS)
-(EVIL-LYN YELPS)

857
00:47:52.125 --> 00:47:54.583
-(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)
-(BREATHES HEAVILY)

858
00:47:58.083 --> 00:48:00.375
ADAM: Where are you taking me?
TEELA: The Royal Guard.

859
00:48:02.166 --> 00:48:03.750
{\an8}Or what's left of us. anyway.

860
00:48:04.750 --> 00:48:07.708
ADAM: The Royal Guard is here?
You've been hiding?

861
00:48:08.125 --> 00:48:09.708
TEELA: Skeletor would
never look for us here.

862
00:48:10.458 --> 00:48:13.750
And now that we have
the Sword. we can beat him.

863
00:48:16.625 --> 00:48:19.875
Keep it close and try not
to draw attention to yourself.

864
00:48:21.958 --> 00:48:23.583
Is that what
people wear on Earth?

865
00:48:25.958 --> 00:48:28.250
Actually. no.
(CHUCKLES) Not really.

866
00:48:32.458 --> 00:48:33.458
TEELA: Don't stare.

867
00:48:34.125 --> 00:48:35.125
(DEVICE BEEPS)

868
00:48:35.250 --> 00:48:36.583
MAN: I have eyes on the Sword.

869
00:48:38.708 --> 00:48:40.291
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

870
00:48:47.958 --> 00:48:50.541
Okay. let me do the talking.

871
00:48:50.708 --> 00:48:52.708
These guys
might be a bit upset with...

872
00:48:54.750 --> 00:48:56.166
Where have you been?

873
00:48:56.291 --> 00:48:57.708
You were supposed
to be on patrol.

874
00:48:57.875 --> 00:48:59.458
Skeletor's goons
are everywhere.

875
00:48:59.625 --> 00:49:01.583
TEELA: I found
the Sword of Power.

876
00:49:03.416 --> 00:49:04.416
What?

877
00:49:05.750 --> 00:49:09.791
There. And the man carrying it
is the son of King Randor.

878
00:49:11.500 --> 00:49:13.500
The long-lost
Prince of Eternos.

879
00:49:16.833 --> 00:49:18.083
Hi. sir.

880
00:49:18.958 --> 00:49:20.041
It's a...

881
00:49:21.250 --> 00:49:22.875
It's a real thrill to be here.

882
00:49:24.208 --> 00:49:25.625
(CHUCKLES)

883
00:49:25.750 --> 00:49:27.125
This is no son of the king.

884
00:49:27.291 --> 00:49:30.125
He is. And he can prove it.

885
00:49:31.750 --> 00:49:33.583
I can. yes. (CHUCKLES)

886
00:49:35.291 --> 00:49:36.291
So...

887
00:49:36.416 --> 00:49:38.541
(AMUSING MUSIC PLAYING)

888
00:49:46.458 --> 00:49:48.875
I remember watching you.
as a kid with my dad.

889
00:49:49.000 --> 00:49:50.375
and seeing you
lead combat drills.

890
00:49:50.500 --> 00:49:51.666
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

891
00:49:51.791 --> 00:49:54.125
What? Is that
an earthquake? What?

892
00:49:56.291 --> 00:49:57.500
Who is this little oik?

893
00:49:58.291 --> 00:49:59.291
Ram Man?

894
00:50:00.750 --> 00:50:01.833
What did you call me?

895
00:50:02.458 --> 00:50:03.458
Ram Man?

896
00:50:03.875 --> 00:50:05.041
You know. because...

897
00:50:05.166 --> 00:50:07.791
Well. I... I called you that
because he looks like a...

898
00:50:07.916 --> 00:50:09.208
Looks like what?

899
00:50:11.958 --> 00:50:14.583
A man who rams.

900
00:50:14.875 --> 00:50:16.708
Imposter. You don't know us.

901
00:50:17.291 --> 00:50:19.291
No. no. no.
I... I do know you.

902
00:50:19.416 --> 00:50:21.916
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)
Well. I've been telling people

903
00:50:22.041 --> 00:50:24.208
about you guys my whole life.

904
00:50:24.375 --> 00:50:26.333
When I was a kid.
I'd make these drawings.

905
00:50:26.458 --> 00:50:27.500
so I'd never forget you.

906
00:50:28.125 --> 00:50:29.916
-Is that so?
-Yeah.

907
00:50:30.041 --> 00:50:31.958
Mm. Well. who am I then?

908
00:50:36.625 --> 00:50:38.791
You're Fisto.

909
00:50:39.333 --> 00:50:41.333
(ALL LAUGHING)

910
00:50:43.833 --> 00:50:46.875
I know that's not your
proper name. but you know.

911
00:50:47.583 --> 00:50:48.708
you fist people. so...

912
00:50:48.833 --> 00:50:51.208
I don't fist people.

913
00:50:51.375 --> 00:50:53.333
I'm pretty sure I saw you
fist a goblin one time.

914
00:50:53.458 --> 00:50:54.583
Adam!

915
00:50:54.750 --> 00:50:56.583
This is the savior of Eternia?

916
00:50:56.750 --> 00:50:59.791
Look. I know. He's not
what I expected either. okay?

917
00:50:59.916 --> 00:51:02.000
But I swear it's him.

918
00:51:02.166 --> 00:51:04.208
I mean. I tracked down
the Sword of Power...

919
00:51:04.333 --> 00:51:06.625
-Let me see this.
-...and it led me to...

920
00:51:06.750 --> 00:51:08.375
-RAM MAN: Stop squirming!
-What are you doing?

921
00:51:08.708 --> 00:51:10.375
-This guy.
-Give it.

922
00:51:10.500 --> 00:51:11.541
(GRUNTS) Teela.

923
00:51:12.875 --> 00:51:13.875
(SNIFFS)

924
00:51:14.958 --> 00:51:16.125
(SIGHS) Thank you.

925
00:51:16.250 --> 00:51:18.000
I'll be honest. I thought
this would go better.

926
00:51:18.958 --> 00:51:20.916
We're going to need a minute
to talk this over.

927
00:51:21.583 --> 00:51:22.583
Sure. Yeah. yeah.

928
00:51:22.708 --> 00:51:23.708
-Let's talk it over.
-No. no. Adam!

929
00:51:23.833 --> 00:51:24.833
Uh-uh-uh.

930
00:51:28.208 --> 00:51:30.291
It's Dina. right? Dina?

931
00:51:30.458 --> 00:51:32.166
DIAN: Dian.
ADAM: Dian.

932
00:51:32.958 --> 00:51:35.416
Dian. Yes! Oh. my God.

933
00:51:35.541 --> 00:51:36.791
All right.
this is super crazy.

934
00:51:36.916 --> 00:51:39.000
but we used to go
to school together. (CHUCKLES)

935
00:51:39.125 --> 00:51:41.750
You used to push me into
the lockers. (SMACKS LIPS)

936
00:51:41.875 --> 00:51:43.583
Aw. Did it hurt?

937
00:51:44.208 --> 00:51:46.208
Well. I... Whoa!

938
00:51:48.625 --> 00:51:50.125
(WHIRRING)

939
00:51:50.250 --> 00:51:51.791
(DOOR LOCKS)

940
00:51:51.916 --> 00:51:56.041
Dian? I think you locked it.
On accident.

941
00:51:58.333 --> 00:51:59.333
Fisto?

942
00:51:59.500 --> 00:52:01.250
It's because
he has a massive...

943
00:52:02.375 --> 00:52:03.833
(SIGHS) I was 10. okay?

944
00:52:03.958 --> 00:52:05.166
TEELA: We have
to get out of here.

945
00:52:09.541 --> 00:52:11.625
It smells
like a urinal in here.

946
00:52:11.750 --> 00:52:13.000
(MAN BELCHES)

947
00:52:13.875 --> 00:52:14.916
Oh.

948
00:52:15.833 --> 00:52:17.666
-It's him.
-MAN: (GROANS) Piss off.

949
00:52:17.791 --> 00:52:19.375
Yep. totally fair.

950
00:52:19.500 --> 00:52:20.708
(MAN SIGHS)

951
00:52:24.875 --> 00:52:26.416
Is that a Class-4 Battlebot?

952
00:52:26.791 --> 00:52:31.291
What? No. it's nothing.
Service bot. Glorified maid.

953
00:52:31.458 --> 00:52:32.458
SERVICE BOT: Charming.

954
00:52:32.583 --> 00:52:34.333
No. Class-4s are the deadliest

955
00:52:34.458 --> 00:52:35.958
super soldiers
ever engineered.

956
00:52:36.083 --> 00:52:40.083
Just one of these bots
is worth about 15 soldiers.

957
00:52:40.375 --> 00:52:42.083
SERVICE BOT: It's actually 20.

958
00:52:42.875 --> 00:52:43.875
Dope.

959
00:52:45.416 --> 00:52:47.125
(DEVICE TRILLS. BEEPS)

960
00:52:48.875 --> 00:52:50.708
It looks
like the Sword of Power.

961
00:52:53.625 --> 00:52:55.166
It's smaller than I thought.

962
00:52:55.291 --> 00:52:57.541
Well. that's just
because my hand is so big.

963
00:52:58.125 --> 00:52:59.666
Your big hand
is your other hand.

964
00:53:01.458 --> 00:53:02.916
Well. this one's
pretty big. too.

965
00:53:03.041 --> 00:53:05.000
That's why the Sword looks
so small when I hold it.

966
00:53:06.291 --> 00:53:08.291
-(DEVICE BEEPS)
-WOMAN: <i>Captain.</i>

967
00:53:09.583 --> 00:53:10.583
Yeah. go ahead.

968
00:53:10.708 --> 00:53:12.541
We may have
a situation out front.

969
00:53:12.666 --> 00:53:15.083
(ENGINES WHIRRING)

970
00:53:15.791 --> 00:53:17.000
-(DOOR THUDS)
-(GRUNTS)

971
00:53:22.541 --> 00:53:23.583
(SCREAMS)

972
00:53:23.708 --> 00:53:25.916
-(DOOR THUDS)
-(RUMBLING)

973
00:53:26.041 --> 00:53:28.583
-(SERVICE BOT SIGHS)
-(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

974
00:53:29.791 --> 00:53:31.250
They're coming for the Sword!

975
00:53:32.583 --> 00:53:33.875
We have to get out of here.

976
00:53:34.000 --> 00:53:36.083
(ROUSING ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

977
00:53:36.208 --> 00:53:37.375
(TUTS)

978
00:53:37.500 --> 00:53:41.625
Miss? You don't belong
down here mopping the floors.

979
00:53:42.375 --> 00:53:43.583
You could join us.

980
00:53:44.000 --> 00:53:45.041
SERVICE BOT: As a servant?

981
00:53:45.166 --> 00:53:46.166
ADAM: No. as a soldier.

982
00:53:46.291 --> 00:53:47.291
Adam. can you please

983
00:53:47.416 --> 00:53:49.083
stop making friends
with the appliances?

984
00:53:49.666 --> 00:53:51.000
-(BURSTING)
-(GRUNTS)

985
00:53:59.541 --> 00:54:00.541
SERVICE BOT: I'll join you

986
00:54:00.666 --> 00:54:02.875
on the condition that
I don't make any food.

987
00:54:03.000 --> 00:54:04.000
I don't wash anything.

988
00:54:04.125 --> 00:54:05.291
and any fluids of any type

989
00:54:05.416 --> 00:54:07.458
that come out of you
are yours to deal with.

990
00:54:07.583 --> 00:54:08.708
Got it?

991
00:54:09.666 --> 00:54:10.708
(CHUCKLES)

992
00:54:12.125 --> 00:54:13.125
TEELA: Wait.

993
00:54:14.208 --> 00:54:15.208
Hold on.

994
00:54:15.875 --> 00:54:17.583
Help me get him up.
I can't leave him.

995
00:54:17.750 --> 00:54:19.541
-What? The drunk guy?
-TEELA: Dad.

996
00:54:19.666 --> 00:54:20.750
Wake up.

997
00:54:20.875 --> 00:54:21.875
(CHUCKLES) Why...

998
00:54:22.541 --> 00:54:23.916
Why'd you call him Dad?

999
00:54:24.083 --> 00:54:25.250
TEELA: He's my dad.

1000
00:54:25.750 --> 00:54:27.416
Dad. wake up.

1001
00:54:27.541 --> 00:54:30.375
DUNCAN: (GROANS) Keep it down.
I'm trying to sleep here.

1002
00:54:30.500 --> 00:54:31.500
Duncan?

1003
00:54:31.625 --> 00:54:32.708
Are you going to help me
get him up or not?

1004
00:54:32.833 --> 00:54:34.750
-(DUNCAN MUTTERS)
-Yeah.

1005
00:54:35.958 --> 00:54:37.583
-Okay.
-(ALL STRAIN)

1006
00:54:37.708 --> 00:54:38.916
Oh. my God. he's heavy.

1007
00:54:40.041 --> 00:54:41.750
-(DUNCAN GROANS)
-(ADAM SIGHS)

1008
00:54:41.875 --> 00:54:42.875
(DUNCAN MUTTERS)

1009
